In a call between Lisa Monaco, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, and President Abdo Rabu Mansour Hadi of Yemen, President Obama's strong support for President Hadi and the Yemeni people was conveyed. Monaco discussed President Hadi's plans to implement the Peace and National Partnership Agreement, including forming a strong government, resolving disagreements peacefully, accelerating the work of the constitutional drafting committee, and scheduling a constitutional referendum and elections. Monaco also condemned members of the Houthi movement and other parties who have resorted to violence, urged reconciliation, and emphasized the United States' determination to designate individuals who threaten Yemen's peace and security. Lastly, Monaco and President Hadi reaffirmed the partnership between the United States and Yemen in countering the threat from al-Qa'ida in the Arabian Peninsula.